	\mu &= \eta \circ \Phi(\mu)\\ 
	& \subseteq \langle \eta, \Phi(\mu) \rangle \\
	& = \langle \eta, {a_1}_{x_1}, \ldots {a_n}_{x_n} \rangle\\
	& \subseteq \mu.
	\end{split} 
	\end{equation*}
	Now, since $L$ is upper well ordered, by Theorem \ref{frat},
	\[ \Phi(\mu) = \bigcup \{ a_x \mid a_x \text{is a non-generator of } \mu \}. \]
